history.text: Hello.
Hi there, do you like Leonardo DiCaprio?
He stars in the Martin Scorsese film "The Wolf of Wall Street", it has a 7.8 score on Rotten Tomatoes
yes, I"m of a middling opinion of him.
Are you a fan?
He plays Jordan Belfort, the star in this one. I like his work
Was the "Wolf of Wall Street" the movie which you read about?
He also produces the movie. It stars Jonah Hall as well
I saw advertisement on TV for that movie. Did the article like it?
The critics were middle of the road about it, it got a C rating by CinemaScore
Did you personally watch the movie?
I saw it in 2014, a year after it came out. Belfort gets pretty heavy into the glamorous life of sex and drugs
Yes, that was my impression from the advertisements of the movie. Small time guy, makes big bucks on Wall Street and his life seems to go adrift with sex, drugs and rock n' roll.
yes that's the gist of it, and he makes a small fortune living the life of fame..for awhile of course
Besides the decadent rock star stuff. Was it a decent movie from character or plot standpoints? Worth watching from that vantage point?
It's pretty engaging, the critic's declared it was epic and irresponsible regarding the budget and all. But the characters are quite interesting
There's a scene that's nestled in the heart of the plot, where Jordan becomes friends with his neighbor, and it takes off from there
Does his friend save him from a bad ending from the sex, drugs and R'nR or does Jordan drag him into that mess and down with him?
or is the neighbor a love interst?
He transfers his money to a Swiss bank account and kind of uses his friends to hide his habit
oh he does come across a love interest, who he leaves his wife for
Ah, does Jordan even have a love interest, old flame he gets rich and revisits or hooker with a heart of gold?
leaves his wife, does that end well?
His neighbor Donnie is actually the one who rats him out
Donnie is the new love interest?
or who he launders the money with.
Naomi is his new love interest, they end up having children, but later divorce and it doesn't end well
haha..kind of life life. I've been there. You say you saw it in 2014 would you see it again for free on Netflix if it was on? Pay to see it again with someone who hadn't seen it before?
No i'm not really into seeing movies twice
touche. thanks for the information and have a lovely day.
